main event: A circular, bright, and glowing object was observed moving back and forth in the sky over Tinker AFB, Oklahoma on September 16, 1952.
interesting points: The object would dim and then return.
The sighting lasted for 45 minutes, from 2155C to 2205C.

The object was observed by multiple witnesses, including a Mrs. [REDACTED] and her brother about 5 miles southeast of Tinker AFB, as well as an observer at the 33rd Air Division Control Center one mile southeast of Tinker AFB.
The weather conditions were reported as 28,000 feet scattered visibility at 15 knots, with winds calm to 5,500 feet WNW at 12-15 knots.
The Air Force was notified and a C-477164 aircraft was sent to the area for identification.
sighted object: a circular, bright, and glowing object
witnesses: multiple, including a Mrs. [REDACTED] and her brother, as well as an observer at the 33rd Air Division Control Center
